<task id="030" project="ai-json-prompt-schema-system">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add configure_prompt_schema Tool Definition</title>
    <phase>4</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api, implement</tags>
    <estimate>2h</estimate>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Add the configure_prompt_schema tool to BuilderToolDefinitions.cs so the Builder Agent can create JPS schemas.</goal>
    <context>
      BuilderToolDefinitions.cs contains OpenAI function tool definitions for the Playbook Builder Agent.
      The new tool allows the agent to create structured prompts with role, task, constraints, typed output fields,
      and optional auto-wired $choices. Tool parameters are simplified vs full JPS — the executor generates
      the complete schema from these inputs.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Follow existing tool definition patterns in BuilderToolDefinitions.cs
      - Parameters: nodeId (required), role, task (required), constraints, outputFields (required), useStructuredOutput, autoWireChoices
      - OutputFields items: name, type (enum: string/number/boolean/array/object), description, enum
      - Include clear description that guides the AI agent on usage
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-json-prompt-schema-system/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-json-prompt-schema-system/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Builder/BuilderToolDefinitions.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read BuilderToolDefinitions.cs for existing tool definition patterns</step>
    <step order="2">Read design.md "New Tool: configure_prompt_schema" section for parameter spec</step>
    <step order="3">Add configure_prompt_schema tool definition following existing patterns</step>
    <step order="4">Add tool name constant to tool constants section</step>
    <step order="5">Register in GetAllTools() and appropriate category</step>
    <step order="6">Verify build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
    <tool>Bash(dotnet build)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Builder/BuilderToolDefinitions.cs (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Tool definition follows existing patterns</criterion>
    <criterion>All parameters defined with correct types and required flags</criterion>
    <criterion>Tool registered in GetAllTools()</criterion>
    <criterion>Project builds without errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
